A coalition of NGOs concerned with the welfare of prisoners and seeking to promote healthcare delivery in the country have raised alarm over the high rate of diabetes and skin infections among inmates of Kuje prison in the FCT. The NGOs comprised Moole Charity Health Foundation (MCF), Health Beyond Barrier Initiative Group(HBBIG) and Conflict Free Nation (CFN). Dr Tolufase Tolulope, the Vice President, Health Beyond Barrier Initiative Group, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Sunday in Abuja that the inmates are suffering mostly fungal skin infections and diabetes. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.